[Merritt, who has some fair experience of rabies incidence in India from visits to that country, makes a fair point in suggesting that the GARC paper may have significantly over estimated the number of rabies cases in India. And thus by extension maybe elsewhere. Informed comment would be appreciated. - Mod.MHJ]
